/**
 * Benefits of the new Camera Configuration Widget:
 * 
 * 1. Modern Table-Based UI:
 *    - Uses SListView with SHeaderRow for professional appearance
 *    - Clear column-based layout: Camera Type | Available | Enabled | Status
 *    - Consistent with UE Editor standards
 * 
 * 2. Better User Experience:
 *    - Color-coded status indicators (Green=Available, Red=Unavailable)
 *    - Clear checkbox controls for enabling/disabling cameras
 *    - Summary information showing active camera count
 *    - Tooltip support for better usability
 * 
 * 3. Improved Code Organization:
 *    - Dedicated widget class for camera configuration
 *    - Structured data using FCameraConfiguration
 *    - Module-ready architecture for future expansion
 *    - Separation of UI and business logic
 * 
 * 4. Enhanced Functionality:
 *    - Real-time configuration validation
 *    - Notification system for user feedback
 *    - Progress tracking capabilities
 *    - Easy integration with future module system
 */

// ============================================================================
// MIGRATION STEPS
// ============================================================================

/**
 * Step 1: Update VCCSimPanel.h
 * - Add #include "Editor/Widgets/CameraConfigWidget.h"
 * - Add TSharedPtr<SCameraConfigWidget> CameraConfigWidget; to private members
 * 
 * Step 2: Update VCCSimPanel_UI.cpp  
 * - Replace CreateCameraSelectPanel() implementation with new code above
 * - Update OnSelectionChanged() to notify camera widget
 * - Remove old camera UI creation methods (CreateCameraStatusRow, CreateCameraStatusBox)
 * 
 * Step 3: Update Build Dependencies
 * - Ensure VCCSimEditor.Build.cs includes necessary modules:
 *   - "Slate", "SlateCore", "EditorStyle", "ToolWidgets"
 * 
 * Step 4: Testing
 * - Verify camera detection works correctly
 * - Test checkbox state changes
 * - Confirm notification system works
 * - Validate with different FlashPawn configurations
 */

